{"url": "http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2016/06/14/orlando-attack-gay-muslims_n_10460860.html", "date": "2016-06-14", "content": "Like their counterparts worldwide, many gay Muslims in the United States have long felt doubly ostracized \u2013 both by the wider national culture and by their co-religionists. But in the days since the massacre of 49 people at a gay nightclub in Orlando, Fla., there have been some signs of acceptance by Islamic organizations and religious institutions more often known for shying away from LGBT issues than for speaking forcefully in defense of gay people.", "title": "How The Orlando Attack Could Mark A Shift For Gay Muslims"}